goal_question: Find the name of the department which has the highest average salary of professors.

goal_question: Show the dates of performances with attending members whose roles are "Violin".

goal_question: Show director with the largest number of show times in total.

goal_question: How many car models are produced by each maker? List the count and the maker full name.

goal_question: Find the captain rank that has no captain in Third-rate ship of the line class.

goal_question: Show the starting years shared by technicians from team "CLE" and "CWS".

goal_question: How many students does LORIA ONDERSMA teaches?

goal_question: What are the durations of the longest and the shortest tracks in milliseconds?

goal_question: Find the first name of the students who permanently live in the country Haiti or have the cell phone number 09700166582.

goal_question: What are id and name of the products whose price is lower than 600 or higher than 900?

goal_question: Find the name of amenities of the dorm where the student with last name Smith is living in.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.amenity_name FROM dorm AS T1 JOIN has_amenity AS T2 ON T1.dormid  =  T2.dormid JOIN dorm_amenity AS T3 ON T2.amenid  =  T3.amenid JOIN lives_in AS T4 ON T4.dormid  =  T1.dormid JOIN student AS T5 ON T5.stuid  =  T4.stuid WHERE T5.lname  =  'Smith'

goal_question: What are the id of students who registered courses or attended courses?
goal_sql: SELECT student_id FROM student_course_registrations UNION SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance

goal_question: Find the number of manufactures that are based in Tokyo or Beijing.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM manufacturers WHERE headquarter  =  'Tokyo' OR headquarter  =  'Beijing'

goal_question: Which parts have more than 2 faults? Show the part name and id.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.part_name ,  T1.part_id FROM Parts AS T1 JOIN Part_Faults AS T2 ON T1.part_id  =  T2.part_id GROUP BY T1.part_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

goal_question: Find the title, credit, and department name of courses that have more than one prerequisites?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.title ,  T1.credits , T1.dept_name FROM course AS T1 JOIN prereq AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id GROUP BY T2.course_id HAVING count(*)  >  1

goal_question: How many students live in HKG or CHI?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Student WHERE city_code  =  "HKG" OR city_code  =  "CHI"

goal_question: Show the name of the customer who has the most orders.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find all procedures which cost more than 1000 or which physician John Wen was trained in.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM procedures WHERE cost  >  1000 UNION SELECT T3.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN trained_in AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.physician JOIN procedures AS T3 ON T3.code  =  T2.treatment WHERE T1.name  =  "John Wen"

goal_question: How many games has each stadium held?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.id ,  count(*) FROM stadium AS T1 JOIN game AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.stadium_id GROUP BY T1.id

goal_question: How many engineers did each staff contact? List both the contact staff name and number of engineers contacted.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.staff_name ,  count(*) FROM Staff AS T1 JOIN Engineer_Visits AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.contact_staff_id GROUP BY T1.staff_name

goal_question: Where does the customer with the first name Linda live? And what is her email?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.address ,  T1.email FROM customer AS T1 JOIN address AS T2 ON T2.address_id  =  T1.address_id WHERE T1.first_name  =  'LINDA'

goal_question: List the customers first and last name of 10 least expensive invoices.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN invoices AS T2 ON T2.customer_id  =  T1.id ORDER BY total LIMIT 10;

goal_question: Please give me a list of cities whose regional population is over 8000000 or under 5000000.
goal_sql: SELECT city FROM city WHERE regional_population  >  10000000 UNION SELECT city FROM city WHERE regional_population  <  5000000

goal_question: List the title of all cartoon directed by "Ben Jones" or "Brandon Vietti".
goal_sql: SELECT Title FROM Cartoon WHERE Directed_by = "Ben Jones" OR Directed_by = "Brandon Vietti";

goal_question: Show the top 3 apartment type codes sorted by the average number of rooms in descending order.

goal_question: How many students have a food allergy?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Allergy_type AS T2 ON T1.allergy  =  T2.allergy WHERE T2.allergytype  =  "food"

goal_question: Find the stories of the building with the largest height.
goal_sql: SELECT Stories FROM buildings ORDER BY Height DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the number of students whose city code is NYC and who have class senator votes in the spring election cycle.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  Class_Senator_Vote WHERE T1.city_code  =  "NYC" AND T2.Election_Cycle  =  "Spring"

goal_question: Which club has the most members majoring in "600"?
goal_sql: SELECT t1.clubname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t3.major  =  "600" GROUP BY t1.clubname ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the minimum and maximum number of bathrooms of all the apartments?
goal_sql: SELECT min(bathroom_count) ,  max(bathroom_count) FROM Apartments

goal_question: Find the name and position of physicians who prescribe some medication whose brand is X?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name ,  T1.position FROM physician AS T1 JOIN prescribes AS T2 ON T1.employeeid = T2.physician JOIN medication AS T3 ON T3.code = T2.medication WHERE T3.Brand  =  "X"

goal_question: Show names of technicians and series of machines they are assigned to repair.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Machine_series FROM repair_assignment AS T1 JOIN machine AS T2 ON T1.machine_id  =  T2.machine_id JOIN technician AS T3 ON T1.technician_ID  =  T3.technician_ID

goal_question: What are the distinct types of the companies that have operated any flights with velocity less than 200?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.type FROM operate_company AS T1 JOIN flight AS t2 ON T1.id  =  T2.company_id WHERE T2.velocity  <  200

goal_question: Which 3 players won the most player awards? List their full name and id.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name_first ,  T1.name_last ,  T1.player_id FROM player AS T1 JOIN player_award AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id GROUP BY T1.player_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3;

goal_question: Find the product names that are colored 'white' but do not have unit of measurement "Handful".
goal_sql: SELECT t1.product_name FROM products AS t1 JOIN ref_product_categories AS t2 ON t1.product_category_code  =  t2.product_category_code JOIN ref_colors AS t3 ON t1.color_code  =  t3.color_code WHERE t3.color_description  =  "white" AND t2.unit_of_measure != "Handful"

goal_question: What is the document name and template id for document with description with the letter 'w' in it?
goal_sql: SELECT document_name ,  template_id FROM Documents WHERE Document_Description LIKE "%w%"

goal_question: Show the distinct apartment numbers of the apartments that have bookings with status code "Confirmed".
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T2.apt_number FROM Apartment_Bookings AS T1 JOIN Apartments AS T2 ON T1.apt_id  =  T2.apt_id WHERE T1.booking_status_code  =  "Confirmed"

goal_question: Find the number of students whose age is older than the average age for each gender.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) ,  sex FROM student WHERE age  >  (SELECT avg(age) FROM student) GROUP BY sex

goal_question: What are the degrees conferred in "San Francisco State University" in 2001.
goal_sql: SELECT degrees FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN degrees AS T2 ON t1.id  =  t2.campus WHERE t1.campus  =  "San Francisco State University" AND t2.year  =  2001

goal_question: How many courses are offered by the Computer Info. Systems department?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM department AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.dept_code  =  T2.dept_code WHERE dept_name  =  "Computer Info. Systems"

goal_question: Find the average age of losers and winners of all matches.

goal_question: List the cities which have more than one airport and number of airports.

goal_question: What is the role code with the largest number of employees?
goal_sql: SELECT role_code FROM Employees GROUP BY role_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: List the names and origins of people who are not body builders.

goal_question: Show the names of authors from college "Florida" or "Temple"
goal_sql: SELECT Author FROM submission WHERE College  =  "Florida" OR College  =  "Temple"

goal_question: Which city lives most of staffs? List the city name and number of staffs.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.city ,  count(*) FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Staff AS T2 ON T1.address_id = T2.staff_address_id GROUP BY T1.city ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: List the names of the dogs of the rarest breed and the treatment dates of them.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name ,  T2.date_of_treatment FROM Dogs AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.dog_id  =  T2.dog_id WHERE T1.breed_code  =  ( SELECT breed_code FROM Dogs GROUP BY breed_code ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1 )

goal_question: Find the number of students for the cities where have more than one student.

goal_question: Find the names of all instructors whose salary is greater than the salary of all instructors in the Biology department.

goal_question: Give me a list of cities whose temperature in Mar is lower than that in July and which have also served as host cities?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.city FROM city AS T1 JOIN temperature AS T2 ON T1.city_id  =  T2.city_id WHERE T2.Mar  <  T2.Jul INTERSECT SELECT T3.city FROM city AS T3 JOIN hosting_city AS T4 ON T3.city_id  =  T4.host_city

goal_question: What is the age of the friend of Zach with longest year relationship?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.age FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.friend WHERE T2.name =  'Zach' AND T2.year  =  (SELECT max(YEAR) FROM PersonFriend WHERE name =  'Zach')

goal_question: How long is the total lesson time took by customer with first name as Rylan and last name as Goodwin?

goal_question: Show the most common apartment type code.

goal_sql: SELECT first_name ,  last_name ,  hire_date FROM employees WHERE department_id  =  (SELECT department_id FROM employees WHERE first_name  =  "Clara")

goal_question: Find the name of instructors who are advisors of the students from the Math department, and sort the results by students' total credit.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.name FROM advisor AS T1 JOIN instructor AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.id JOIN student AS T3 ON T1.s_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.dept_name  =  'Math' ORDER BY T3.tot_cred

goal_question: Find the top 3 artists who have the largest number of songs works whose language is Bangla.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.artist_name FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name WHERE T2.languages  =  "bangla" GROUP BY T2.artist_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3

goal_question: Find the name and gender of the staff who has been assigned the job of Sales Person but never Clerical Staff.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T1.staff_gender FROM staff AS T1 JOIN Staff_Department_Assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.job_title_code  =  "Sales Person" EXCEPT SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T1.staff_gender FROM staff AS T1 JOIN Staff_Department_Assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.job_title_code  =  "Clerical Staff"

goal_question: Find the name and address of the customers who have both New and Pending orders.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.customer_name ,  T1.customer_address FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status_code  =  "New" INTERSECT SELECT T1.customer_name ,  T1.customer_address FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status_code  =  "Pending"

goal_question: What are the names of enzymes in the medicine named 'Amisulpride' that can serve as an 'inhibitor'?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM enzyme AS T1 JOIN medicine_enzyme_interaction AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.enzyme_id JOIN medicine AS T3 ON T2.medicine_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'Amisulpride' AND T2.interaction_type  =  'inhibitor'

goal_question: Find the organisation ids and details of the organisations which are involved in
goal_sql: SELECT T2.organisation_id ,  T2.organisation_details FROM Grants AS T1 JOIN Organisations AS T2 ON T1.organisation_id  =  T2.organisation_id GROUP BY T2.organisation_id HAVING sum(T1.grant_amount)  >  6000

goal_question: Find the maximum and total number of followers of all users.
goal_sql: SELECT max(followers) ,  sum(followers) FROM user_profiles

goal_question: List the time of elimination of the wrestlers with largest days held.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Time FROM elimination AS T1 JOIN wrestler AS T2 ON T1.Wrestler_ID  =  T2.Wrestler_ID ORDER BY T2.Days_held DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many students attend course English?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_attendance AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id WHERE T1.course_name = "English"

goal_question: What is the average earnings of poker players with height higher than 200?
goal_sql: SELECT avg(T2.Earnings) FROM people AS T1 JOIN poker_player AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID WHERE T1.Height  >  200

goal_question: Find the name of the department that has no students minored in?
goal_sql: SELECT DName FROM DEPARTMENT EXCEPT SELECT T1.DName FROM DEPARTMENT AS T1 JOIN MINOR_IN AS T2 ON T1.DNO  =  T2.DNO

goal_question: What is the name of the most recent movie?
goal_sql: SELECT title FROM Movie WHERE YEAR  =  (SELECT max(YEAR) FROM Movie)

goal_question: Find names of the document without any images.
goal_sql: SELECT document_name FROM documents EXCEPT SELECT t1.document_name FROM documents AS t1 JOIN document_sections AS t2 ON t1.document_code  =  t2.document_code JOIN document_sections_images AS t3 ON t2.section_id  =  t3.section_id

goal_question: Find the market shares and names of furnitures which no any company is producing in our records.
goal_sql: SELECT Market_Rate ,  name FROM furniture WHERE Furniture_ID NOT IN (SELECT Furniture_ID FROM furniture_manufacte)

goal_question: How many events did not have any participants?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM EVENTS WHERE event_id NOT IN (SELECT event_id FROM Participants_in_Events)

goal_question: For grants with both documents described as 'Regular' and documents described as 'Initial Application', list its start date.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.grant_start_date FROM Grants AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.grant_id  =  T2.grant_id JOIN Document_Types AS T3 ON T2.document_type_code  =  T3.document_type_code WHERE T3.document_description  =  'Regular' INTERSECT SELECT T1.grant_start_date FROM Grants AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.grant_id  =  T2.grant_id JOIN Document_Types AS T3 ON T2.document_type_code  =  T3.document_type_code WHERE T3.document_description  =  'Initial Application'

goal_question: In which year were most departments established?
goal_sql: SELECT creation FROM department GROUP BY creation ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the title and maximum price of each film?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.title ,  max(T1.price) FROM schedule AS T1 JOIN film AS T2 ON T1.film_id  =  T2.film_id GROUP BY T1.film_id

goal_question: Find the name and age of all males in order of their age.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM Person WHERE gender  =  'male' ORDER BY age

goal_question: What is the name of the artist who joined latest?
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM artist ORDER BY year_join DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the id of courses which are registered or attended by student whose id is 121?
goal_sql: SELECT course_id FROM student_course_registrations WHERE student_id = 121 UNION SELECT course_id FROM student_course_attendance WHERE student_id = 121

goal_question: Find the distinct names of all wines that have prices higher than some wines from John Anthony winery.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT Name FROM WINE WHERE Price  >  (SELECT min(Price) FROM wine WHERE Winery  =  "John Anthony")

goal_question: Show names for all aircrafts of which John Williams has certificates.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.name FROM Employee AS T1 JOIN Certificate AS T2 ON T1.eid  =  T2.eid JOIN Aircraft AS T3 ON T3.aid  =  T2.aid WHERE T1.name  =  "John Williams"

goal_question: what are the names and classes of the ships that do not have any captain yet?
goal_sql: SELECT name ,  CLASS FROM ship WHERE ship_id NOT IN (SELECT ship_id FROM captain)

goal_question: Show the countries that have managers of age above 50 or below 46.
goal_sql: SELECT Country FROM manager WHERE Age  >  50 OR Age  <  46

goal_question: For each building, show the name of the building and the number of institutions in it.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name ,  count(*) FROM building AS T1 JOIN institution AS T2 ON T1.building_id  =  T2.building_id GROUP BY T1.building_id

goal_question: What are the id and address of the shops which have a happy hour in May?
goal_sql: SELECT t1.address ,  t1.shop_id FROM shop AS t1 JOIN happy_hour AS t2 ON t1.shop_id  =  t2.shop_id WHERE MONTH  =  'May'

goal_question: Which document type is described with the prefix 'Initial'?
goal_sql: SELECT document_type_code FROM Document_Types WHERE document_description LIKE 'Initial%'

goal_question: Show the distinct leader names of colleges associated with members from country "Canada".
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Leader_Name FROM college AS T1 JOIN member AS T2 ON T1.College_ID  =  T2.College_ID WHERE T2.Country  =  "Canada"

goal_question: Show the most common type code across products.
goal_sql: SELECT Product_Type_Code FROM Products GROUP BY Product_Type_Code ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the id and number of shops for the company that produces the most expensive furniture.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.manufacturer_id ,  t1.num_of_shops FROM manufacturer AS t1 JOIN furniture_manufacte AS t2 ON t1.manufacturer_id  =  t2.manufacturer_id ORDER BY t2.Price_in_Dollar DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: List the race class with at least two races.
goal_sql: SELECT CLASS FROM race GROUP BY CLASS HAVING count(*)  >=  2

goal_question: How many trains have 'Express' in their names?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM train WHERE name LIKE "%Express%"

goal_question: Please show the songs that have result "nominated" at music festivals.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Song FROM music_festival AS T1 JOIN volume AS T2 ON T1.Volume  =  T2.Volume_ID WHERE T1.Result  =  "Nominated"

goal_question: What are the distinct name, location and products of the enzymes which has any 'inhibitor' interaction?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name ,  T1.location ,  T1.product FROM enzyme AS T1 JOIN medicine_enzyme_interaction AS T2 ON T2.enzyme_id  =  T1.id WHERE T2.interaction_type  =  'inhibitor'

goal_question: List the names, color descriptions and product descriptions of products with category "Herbs".
goal_sql: SELECT T1.product_name ,  T2.color_description ,  T1.product_description FROM products AS T1 JOIN Ref_colors AS T2 ON T1.color_code  =  T2.color_code WHERE product_category_code  =  "Herbs"

goal_question: Find the total amount claimed in the most recently created document.
goal_sql: SELECT sum(t1.amount_claimed) FROM claim_headers AS t1 JOIN claims_documents AS t2 ON t1.claim_header_id  =  t2.claim_id WHERE t2.created_date  =  (SELECT created_date FROM claims_documents ORDER BY created_date LIMIT 1)

goal_question: Show the names of clubs that have players with position "Right Wing".
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM club AS T1 JOIN player AS T2 ON T1.Club_ID  =  T2.Club_ID WHERE T2.Position  =  "Right Wing"

goal_question: Show publishers with a book published in 1989 and a book in 1990.
goal_sql: SELECT publisher FROM book_club WHERE YEAR  =  1989 INTERSECT SELECT publisher FROM book_club WHERE YEAR  =  1990

goal_question: List the name of ships that are not involved in any mission
goal_sql: SELECT Name FROM ship WHERE Ship_ID NOT IN (SELECT Ship_ID FROM mission)

goal_sql: SELECT rid FROM routes WHERE dst_apid IN (SELECT apid FROM airports WHERE country  =  'United States') AND src_apid IN (SELECT apid FROM airports WHERE country  =  'United States')

goal_question: How many distinct locations have the things with service detail 'Unsatisfied' been located in?

goal_question: Which months have more than 2 happy hours?
goal_sql: SELECT MONTH FROM happy_hour GROUP BY MONTH HAVING count(*)  >  2

goal_question: How many settlements does each claim correspond to? List the claim id and the number of settlements.

goal_sql: SELECT t1.store_name FROM store AS t1 JOIN store_district AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id WHERE district_id  =  (SELECT district_id FROM district ORDER BY city_population DESC LIMIT 1)

goal_question: Show names for artists without any exhibition.

goal_question: Find the last names of faculties in building Barton in alphabetic order.

goal_sql: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.job_id FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id WHERE T2.department_name  =  'Finance'

goal_sql: SELECT T1.claim_id ,  T1.date_claim_made ,  T1.Date_Claim_Settled FROM Claims AS T1 JOIN Settlements AS T2 ON T1.Claim_id  =  T2.Claim_id GROUP BY T1.claim_id HAVING count(*)  =  1

goal_question: What is the "active to date" of the latest contact channel used by "Tillman Ernser"?

goal_question: Find the average number of followers for the users who had some tweets.

goal_question: What are the names of schools with the top 3 largest size?

goal_question: Find the first name of students living in city PHL whose age is between 20 and 25.

goal_question: Show the headquarters that have at least two companies.

goal_question: Find the average height and weight for all males (sex is M).

goal_question: How many products were not included in any order?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM products WHERE product_id NOT IN ( SELECT product_id FROM Order_items )

goal_question: What is the total number of people living in the nations that do not use English?

goal_question: What is the status code, mobile phone number and email address of customer with last name as Kohler or first name as Marina?

goal_question: Which state has the most customers?

goal_question: What is the smallest weight of the car produced with 8 cylinders on 1974?

goal_question: What are the average, maximum, and minimum number of floors for all buildings?

goal_question: What is the most common birth place of people?

goal_question: Show the types of ships that have both ships with tonnage larger than 6000 and ships with tonnage smaller than 4000.

Systems'

goal_question: What are the names of the songs whose rating is below the rating of all songs in English?
goal_sql: SELECT song_name FROM song WHERE rating  <   (SELECT min(rating) FROM song WHERE languages  =  'english')

goal_question: What is the location with the most cinemas opened in year 2010 or later?
goal_sql: SELECT LOCATION FROM cinema WHERE openning_year  >=  2010 GROUP BY LOCATION ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the entry name of the most expensive catalog (in USD)?
goal_sql: SELECT catalog_entry_name FROM catalog_contents ORDER BY price_in_dollars DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: List the top 10 customers by total gross sales. List customers' first and last name and total gross sales.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  SUM(T2.total) FROM customers AS T1 JOIN invoices AS T2 ON T2.customer_id  =  T1.id GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY SUM(T2.total) DESC LIMIT 10;

goal_question: Show the names of members in ascending order of their rank in rounds.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Name FROM member AS T1 JOIN round AS T2 ON T1.Member_ID  =  T2.Member_ID ORDER BY Rank_in_Round ASC

goal_question: What are the names of products whose availability equals to 1?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.product_name FROM view_product_availability AS T1 JOIN products_for_hire AS T2 ON T1.product_id  =  T2.product_id WHERE T1.available_yn  =  1

goal_question: What are the distinct name, location and products of the enzymes which has any 'inhibitor' interaction?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name ,  T1.location ,  T1.product FROM enzyme AS T1 JOIN medicine_enzyme_interaction AS T2 ON T2.enzyme_id  =  T1.id WHERE T2.interaction_type  =  'inhibitor'

goal_question: What are the names of the nations with the 3 lowest populations?
goal_sql: SELECT Name FROM country ORDER BY Population ASC LIMIT 3

goal_question: Show the names of students who have a grade higher than 5 and have at least 2 friends.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.name FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.grade  >  5 GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

goal_question: Find the names of songs whose genre is modern or language is English.
goal_sql: SELECT song_name FROM song WHERE genre_is  =  "modern" OR languages  =  "english"

goal_question: Find the name of the customers who have at most two orders.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.customer_name FROM orders AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id GROUP BY T2.customer_id HAVING count(*)  <=  2

goal_question: Find the average and oldest age for students with different sex.
goal_sql: SELECT avg(age) ,  max(age) ,  sex FROM student GROUP BY sex

goal_question: Find the names of students who have taken any course in the fall semester of year 2003.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM student WHERE id IN (SELECT id FROM takes WHERE semester  =  'Fall' AND YEAR  =  2003)

goal_question: Who is enrolled in a Bachelor degree program? List the first name, middle name, last name.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.first_name ,  T1.middle_name ,  T1.last_name FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id JOIN Degree_Programs AS T3 ON T2.degree_program_id  =  T3.degree_program_id WHERE T3.degree_summary_name  =  'Bachelor'

goal_question: Which model has the most version(make) of cars?

goal_question: Show all official native languages that contain the word "English".

goal_question: List the campus that have between 600 and 1000 faculty lines in year 2004.

goal_question: Show names of teachers and the number of courses they teach.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM course_arrange AS T1 JOIN teacher AS T2 ON T1.Teacher_ID  =  T2.Teacher_ID GROUP BY T2.Name

goal_question: What is the name of the entrepreneur with the greatest weight?

goal_question: Find the checking balance of the accounts whose savings balance is higher than the average savings balance.

goal_question: Return the gender and name of artist who produced the song with the lowest resolution.

goal_question: Find the name, city, and country of the airport that has the lowest altitude.

goal_question: What are the hometowns of gymnasts and the corresponding number of gymnasts?

goal_question: Display the first and last name, and salary for those employees whose first name is ending with the letter m.

goal_question: What is the most common major among female (sex is F) students?

goal_question: List the grape, winery and year of the wines whose price is bigger than 100 ordered by year.
goal_sql: SELECT Grape ,  Winery ,  YEAR FROM WINE WHERE Price  >   100 ORDER BY YEAR

goal_question: What is the largest payment amount?
goal_sql: SELECT amount FROM payment ORDER BY amount DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show the name of employees with three lowest salaries.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM Employee ORDER BY salary ASC LIMIT 3

goal_question: What is the average sales of the journals that have an editor whose work type is 'Photo'?
goal_sql: SELECT avg(T1.sales) FROM journal AS T1 JOIN journal_committee AS T2 ON T1.journal_ID  =  T2.journal_ID WHERE T2.work_type  =  'Photo'

goal_question: How many flights arriving in Aberdeen city?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM FLIGHTS AS T1 JOIN AIRPORTS AS T2 ON T1.DestAirport  =  T2.AirportCode WHERE T2.City  =  "Aberdeen"

goal_question: Which cmi cross reference id is not related to any parking taxes?
goal_sql: SELECT cmi_cross_ref_id FROM cmi_cross_references EXCEPT SELECT cmi_cross_ref_id FROM parking_fines

goal_question: Find the names of the customers who have an deputy policy.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT t2.customer_details FROM policies AS t1 JOIN customers AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id WHERE t1.policy_type_code  =  "Deputy"

goal_question: Which employee has showed up in most circulation history documents. List the employee's name and the number of drafts and copies.
goal_sql: SELECT Employees.employee_name , count(*) FROM Employees JOIN Circulation_History ON Circulation_History.employee_id = Employees.employee_id GROUP BY Circulation_History.document_id , Circulation_History.draft_number , Circulation_History.copy_number ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: What are the African countries that have a  population less than any country in Asia?
goal_sql: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Africa"  AND population  <  (SELECT max(population) FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia")

goal_question: Show the name of the party that has at least two records.
goal_sql: SELECT Party FROM party GROUP BY Party HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

goal_question: Retrieve the title of the paper that has the largest number of authors.
goal_sql: SELECT t2.title FROM authorship AS t1 JOIN papers AS t2 ON t1.paperid  =  t2.paperid WHERE t1.authorder  =  (SELECT max(authorder) FROM authorship)

goal_question: Show all church names except for those that had a wedding in year 2015.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM church EXCEPT SELECT T1.name FROM church AS T1 JOIN wedding AS T2 ON T1.church_id  =  T2.church_id WHERE T2.year  =  2015

goal_question: Which first names are used for professionals or owners but are not used as dog names?
goal_sql: SELECT first_name FROM Professionals UNION SELECT first_name FROM Owners EXCEPT SELECT name FROM Dogs

goal_question: Find the average height and weight for all males (sex is M).
goal_sql: SELECT avg(height) ,  avg(weight) FROM people WHERE sex  =  'M'

goal_question: Find the name of the makers that produced some cars in the year of 1970?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';

goal_question: Show the account name and other account detail for all accounts by the customer with first name Meaghan and last name Keeling.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.account_name ,  T1.other_account_details FROM Accounts AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.customer_first_name  =  "Meaghan" AND T2.customer_last_name  =  "Keeling"

goal_question: What are the name and payment method of customers who have both mailshots in 'Order' outcome and mailshots in 'No Response' outcome.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.customer_name ,  T2.payment_method FROM mailshot_customers AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T1.outcome_code  =  'Order' INTERSECT SELECT T2.customer_name ,  T2.payment_method FROM mailshot_customers AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T1.outcome_code  =  'No Response'

goal_question: What is id of the city that hosted events in the most recent year?
goal_sql: SELECT host_city FROM hosting_city ORDER BY YEAR DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many services has each resident requested? List the resident id, details, and the count in descending order of the count.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.resident_id ,  T1.other_details ,  count(*) FROM Residents AS T1 JOIN Residents_Services AS T2 ON T1.resident_id  =  T2.resident_id GROUP BY T1.resident_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC

goal_question: Show the number of audience in year 2008 or 2010.
goal_sql: SELECT Num_of_Audience FROM festival_detail WHERE YEAR  =  2008 OR YEAR  =  2010

goal_question: Find the ids and names of stations from which at least 200 trips started.
goal_sql: SELECT start_station_id ,  start_station_name FROM trip GROUP BY start_station_name HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  200

goal_question: Find the id and last name of the student that has the most behavior incidents?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.student_id ,  T2.last_name FROM Behavior_Incident AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: find the id of tv channels that do not play any cartoon directed by Ben Jones.
goal_sql: SELECT id FROM TV_Channel EXCEPT SELECT channel FROM cartoon WHERE directed_by  =  'Ben Jones'

goal_question: Find the names of stadiums that the most swimmers have been to.
goal_sql: SELECT t3.name FROM record AS t1 JOIN event AS t2 ON t1.event_id  =  t2.id JOIN stadium AS t3 ON t3.id  =  t2.stadium_id GROUP BY t2.stadium_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show the starting years shared by technicians from team "CLE" and "CWS".
goal_sql: SELECT Starting_Year FROM technician WHERE Team  =  "CLE" INTERSECT SELECT Starting_Year FROM technician WHERE Team  =  "CWS"

goal_question: Find the names of stores whose number products is more than the average number of products.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM shop WHERE number_products  >  (SELECT avg(number_products) FROM shop)

goal_question: What is the average latitude and longitude of stations located in San Jose city?
goal_sql: SELECT avg(lat) ,  avg(long) FROM station WHERE city  =  "San Jose"

goal_question: Find id of the candidate whose email is stanley.monahan@example.org?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.candidate_id FROM people AS T1 JOIN candidates AS T2 ON T1.person_id = T2.candidate_id WHERE T1.email_address = "stanley.monahan@example.org"

goal_question: Find the names of districts where have both city mall and village store type stores.
goal_sql: SELECT t3.District_name FROM store AS t1 JOIN store_district AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id JOIN district AS t3 ON t2.district_id  =  t3.district_id WHERE t1.Type  =  "City Mall" INTERSECT SELECT t3.District_name FROM store AS t1 JOIN store_district AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id JOIN district AS t3 ON t2.district_id  =  t3.district_id WHERE t1.Type  =  "Village Store"

goal_question: What are the names and scores of wines that are made of white color grapes?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Name ,   T2.Score FROM GRAPES AS T1 JOIN WINE AS T2 ON T1.Grape  =  T2.Grape WHERE T1.Color  =  "White"

goal_question: For each phone, show its names and total number of stocks.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Name ,  sum(T1.Num_of_stock) FROM phone_market AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Phone_ID  =  T2.Phone_ID GROUP BY T2.Name

goal_question: What is the largest and smallest customer codes?
goal_sql: SELECT max(customer_code) ,  min(customer_code) FROM Customers

goal_question: What is the location code with the most documents?
goal_sql: SELECT location_code FROM Document_locations GROUP BY location_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the number of routes from the United States to Canada.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM routes WHERE dst_apid IN (SELECT apid FROM airports WHERE country  =  'Canada') AND src_apid IN (SELECT apid FROM airports WHERE country  =  'United States')

goal_question: How many students attend course English?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_attendance AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id WHERE T1.course_name = "English"

goal_question: Find all the catalog publishers whose name contains "Murray"
goal_sql: SELECT distinct(catalog_publisher) FROM catalogs WHERE catalog_publisher LIKE "%Murray%"

goal_question: What are the names of all songs that have a lower rating than some song of blues genre?
goal_sql: SELECT song_name FROM song WHERE rating  <  (SELECT max(rating) FROM song WHERE genre_is  =  "blues")

goal_question: How many albums does Billy Cobham has?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM albums AS T1 JOIN artists AS T2 ON  T1.artist_id = T2.id WHERE T2.name = "Billy Cobham";

goal_question: Find the unit of measurement and product category code of product named "chervil".
goal_sql: SELECT t2.unit_of_measure ,  t2.product_category_code FROM products AS t1 JOIN ref_product_categories AS t2 ON t1.product_category_code  =  t2.product_category_code WHERE t1.product_name  =  "chervil"

goal_question: Find the number of characteristics that the product "flax" has.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM products AS t1 JOIN product_characteristics AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id JOIN CHARACTERISTICS AS t3 ON t2.characteristic_id  =  t3.characteristic_id WHERE t1.product_name  =  "flax"

goal_question: How many Annual Meeting events happened in the United Kingdom region?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM region AS t1 JOIN party AS t2 ON t1.region_id  =  t2.region_id JOIN party_events AS t3 ON t2.party_id  =  t3.party_id WHERE t1.region_name  =  "United Kingdom" AND t3.Event_Name  =  "Annaual Meeting"

goal_question: How many engineer visits are required at most for a single fault log? List the number and the log entry id.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.fault_log_entry_id FROM Fault_Log AS T1 JOIN Engineer_Visits AS T2 ON T1.fault_log_entry_id  =  T2.fault_log_entry_id GROUP BY T1.fault_log_entry_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the name of the document with the most number of sections?
goal_sql: SELECT t1.document_name FROM documents AS t1 JOIN document_sections AS t2 ON t1.document_code  =  t2.document_code GROUP BY t1.document_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Which city has most number of departing flights?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.City FROM AIRPORTS AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.AirportCode  =  T2.SourceAirport GROUP BY T1.City ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the tax source system code related to the benefits and overpayments? List the code and the benifit id, order by benifit id.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.source_system_code ,  T2.council_tax_id FROM CMI_Cross_References AS T1 JOIN Benefits_Overpayments AS T2 ON T1.cmi_cross_ref_id  =  T2.cmi_cross_ref_id ORDER BY T2.council_tax_id

goal_question: List the grape, appelation and name of wines whose score is higher than 93 ordered by Name.
goal_sql: SELECT Grape ,  Appelation ,  Name FROM WINE WHERE Score  >  93 ORDER BY Name

goal_question: Which district has the least area?
goal_sql: SELECT district_name FROM district ORDER BY city_area ASC LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many different roles are there in the club "Bootup Baltimore"?
goal_sql: SELECT count(DISTINCT t2.position) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Bootup Baltimore"

goal_question: Find the official names of cities with population bigger than 1500 or smaller than 500.
goal_sql: SELECT Official_Name FROM city WHERE Population  >  1500 OR Population  <  500

goal_question: What is the total number of purchases for members with level 6?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM purchase AS T1 JOIN member AS T2 ON T1.member_id  =  T2.member_id WHERE T2.level  =  6

goal_question: List the names of products that are not in any event.
goal_sql: SELECT Product_Name FROM Products WHERE Product_ID NOT IN (SELECT Product_ID FROM Products_in_Events)

goal_question: Find the total amount of loans offered by each bank branch.
goal_sql: SELECT sum(amount) ,  T1.bname FROM bank AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.branch_id  =  T2.branch_id GROUP BY T1.bname

goal_question: What are the countries where either English or Dutch is the official language?
goal_sql: SELECT * FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" AND IsOfficial  =  "T" UNION SELECT * FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "Dutch" AND IsOfficial  =  "T"

goal_question: How many countries do not have an roller coaster longer than 3000?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM country WHERE country_id NOT IN ( SELECT country_id FROM roller_coaster WHERE LENGTH  >  3000 )

goal_question: List the names of the customers who have once bought product "food".
goal_sql: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 JOIN order_items AS T3 JOIN products AS T4 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id AND T2.order_id = T3.order_id AND T3.product_id = T4.product_id WHERE T4.product_name = "food" GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  1

goal_question: Show institution names along with the number of proteins for each institution.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.institution ,  count(*) FROM institution AS T1 JOIN protein AS T2 ON T1.institution_id  =  T2.institution_id GROUP BY T1.institution_id

goal_question: Find the name and checking balance of the account with the lowest saving balance.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.balance ,  T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid JOIN savings AS T3 ON T1.custid  =  T3.custid ORDER BY T3.balance LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the Asian countries which have a population larger than that of any country in Africa?
goal_sql: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia"  AND population  >  (SELECT min(population) FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Africa")

goal_question: What are the ids of stations that have latitude above 37.4 and never had bike availability below 7?
goal_sql: SELECT id FROM station WHERE lat  >  37.4 EXCEPT SELECT station_id FROM status GROUP BY station_id HAVING min(bikes_available)  <  7

goal_question: What is the name of country that has the shortest life expectancy in Asia?
goal_sql: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia" ORDER BY LifeExpectancy LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many female people are older than 30 in our record?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM people WHERE is_male  =  'F' AND age  >  30

goal_question: Find the name of route that has the highest number of deliveries.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.route_name FROM Delivery_Routes AS t1 JOIN Delivery_Route_Locations AS t2 ON t1.route_id  =  t2.route_id GROUP BY t1.route_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show student ids who are female and play football.
goal_sql: SELECT StuID FROM Student WHERE sex  =  'F' INTERSECT SELECT StuID FROM Sportsinfo WHERE sportname  =  "Football"

goal_question: Find the name of tracks which are in Movies playlist but not in music playlist.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN playlist_tracks AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.track_id JOIN playlists AS T3 ON T2.playlist_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'Movies' EXCEPT SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN playlist_tracks AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.track_id JOIN playlists AS T3 ON T2.playlist_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'Music'

goal_question: Show the names of the drivers without a school bus.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM driver WHERE driver_id NOT IN (SELECT driver_id FROM school_bus)

goal_question: Find all the films longer than 100 minutes, or rated PG, except those who cost more than 200 for replacement. List the titles.

goal_question: what is id of students who registered some courses but the least number of courses in these students?
goal_sql: SELECT student_id FROM student_course_registrations GROUP BY student_id ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the maximum training hours for the students whose training hours is greater than 1000 in different positions?
goal_sql: SELECT max(T1.HS) ,  pPos FROM player AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.pID  =  T2.pID WHERE T1.HS  >  1000 GROUP BY T2.pPos

goal_question: List name of all tracks in Balls to the Wall.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.name FROM albums AS T1 JOIN tracks AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.genre_id WHERE T1.title = "Balls to the Wall";

goal_question: Show the players and years played for players from team "Columbus Crew".
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Player , T1.Years_Played FROM player AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.Team  =  T2.Team_id WHERE T2.Name  =  "Columbus Crew"

goal_question: What are the id and zip code of the address with the highest monthly rental?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.address_id ,  T1.zip_postcode FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Student_Addresses AS T2 ON T1.address_id  =  T2.address_id ORDER BY monthly_rental DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: what are the names of the channels that broadcast in both morning and night?
goal_sql: SELECT t1.name FROM channel AS t1 JOIN broadcast AS t2 ON t1.channel_id  =  t2.channel_id WHERE t2.time_of_day  =  'Morning' INTERSECT SELECT t1.name FROM channel AS t1 JOIN broadcast AS t2 ON t1.channel_id  =  t2.channel_id WHERE t2.time_of_day  =  'Night'

goal_question: What are the id and name of the stations that have ever had more than 12 bikes available?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.id ,  T1.name FROM station AS T1 JOIN status AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.station_id WHERE T2.bikes_available  >  12

goal_question: Show all storm names affecting region "Denmark".
goal_sql: SELECT T3.name FROM affected_region AS T1 JOIN region AS T2 ON T1.region_id  =  T2.region_id JOIN storm AS T3 ON T1.storm_id  =  T3.storm_id WHERE T2.region_name  =  'Denmark'

goal_question: display those employees who contain a letter z to their first name and also display their last name, city.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T3.city FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id JOIN locations AS T3 ON T2.location_id  =  T3.location_id WHERE T1.first_name LIKE '%z%'

goal_question: What are the maximum and minimum number of cows across all farms.
goal_sql: SELECT max(Cows) ,  min(Cows) FROM farm

goal_question: Find the countries that have never participated in any competition with Friendly type.
goal_sql: SELECT country FROM competition EXCEPT SELECT country FROM competition WHERE competition_type  =  'Friendly'

goal_question: Show the names of employees with role name Editor.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.employee_name FROM Employees AS T1 JOIN ROLES AS T2 ON T1.role_code  =  T2.role_code WHERE T2.role_name  =  "Editor"

goal_question: Find the state which has the most number of customers.
goal_sql: SELECT state FROM bank GROUP BY state ORDER BY sum(no_of_customers) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the name of the swimmer who has at least 2 records.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.name FROM swimmer AS t1 JOIN record AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.swimmer_id GROUP BY t2.swimmer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

goal_question: For directors who had more than one movie, return the titles and produced years of all movies directed by them.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.title ,  T1.year FROM Movie AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.director  =  T2.director WHERE T1.title != T2.title

goal_question: Show the transaction type descriptions and dates if the share count is smaller than 10.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.transaction_type_description ,  T2.date_of_transaction FROM Ref_Transaction_Types AS T1 JOIN TRANSACTIONS AS T2 ON T1.transaction_type_code  =  T2.transaction_type_code WHERE T2.share_count  <  10

goal_question: Find the names of accounts whose checking balance is above the average checking balance, but savings balance is below the average savings balance.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid WHERE T2.balance  >  (SELECT avg(balance) FROM checking) INTERSECT SELECT T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN savings AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid WHERE T2.balance  <  (SELECT avg(balance) FROM savings)

goal_question: what is the name and age of the youngest winning pilot?
goal_sql: SELECT t1.name ,  t1.age FROM pilot AS t1 JOIN MATCH AS t2 ON t1.pilot_id  =  t2.winning_pilot ORDER BY t1.age LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the storm name and max speed which affected the greatest number of regions?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.max_speed FROM storm AS T1 JOIN affected_region AS T2 ON T1.storm_id  =  T2.storm_id GROUP BY T1.storm_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Which employee has showed up in most circulation history documents. List the employee's name and the number of drafts and copies.
goal_sql: SELECT Employees.employee_name , count(*) FROM Employees JOIN Circulation_History ON Circulation_History.employee_id = Employees.employee_id GROUP BY Circulation_History.document_id , Circulation_History.draft_number , Circulation_History.copy_number ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: What is the money rank of the poker player with the highest earnings?
goal_sql: SELECT Money_Rank FROM poker_player ORDER BY Earnings DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show the apartment type code that has the largest number of total rooms, together with the number of bathrooms and number of bedrooms.
goal_sql: SELECT apt_type_code ,  bathroom_count ,  bedroom_count FROM Apartments GROUP BY apt_type_code ORDER BY sum(room_count) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Which products has been complained by the customer who has filed least amount of complaints?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT t1.product_name FROM products AS t1 JOIN complaints AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id JOIN customers AS t3 GROUP BY t3.customer_id ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

goal_question: A list of the top 8 countries by gross/total invoice size. List country name and gross invoice size.
goal_sql: SELECT billing_country ,  SUM(total) FROM invoices GROUP BY billing_country ORDER BY SUM(total) DESC LIMIT 8;

goal_question: What is the name of the claim processing stage that most of the claims are on?
goal_sql: SELECT t2.claim_status_name FROM claims_processing AS t1 JOIN claims_processing_stages AS t2 ON t1.claim_stage_id  =  t2.claim_stage_id GROUP BY t1.claim_stage_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_sql: SELECT T1.date_order_placed FROM orders AS T1 JOIN shipments AS T2 ON T1.order_id = T2.order_id WHERE T2.invoice_number = 10

goal_question: Find the name of the products that are not using the most frequently-used max page size.
goal_sql: SELECT product FROM product WHERE product != (SELECT max_page_size FROM product GROUP BY max_page_size ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1)

goal_question: List the name of the company that produced more than one phone model.

goal_question: Find the city and name of bank branches that provide business loans.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.bname ,  T1.city FROM bank AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.branch_id  =  T2.branch_id WHERE T2.loan_type  =  'Business'

goal_question: Show the themes of parties and the names of the party hosts.

goal_question: Retrieve the country that has published the most papers.

goal_question: Find the names of all stores in Khanewal District.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.store_name FROM store AS t1 JOIN store_district AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id JOIN district AS t3 ON t2.district_id  =  t3.district_id WHERE t3.district_name  =  "Khanewal District"

goal_question: In which season and which stadium did any player have an injury of 'Foot injury' or 'Knee problem'?

goal_question: Show ids for all templates not used by any document.
goal_sql: SELECT template_id FROM Templates EXCEPT SELECT template_id FROM Documents

goal_question: Find the distinct last names of all the students who have president votes and whose advisor is 8741.

goal_question: What are the distinct cross reference source system codes which are related to the master customer details 'Gottlieb, Becker and Wyman'?

goal_question: What is the maximum, minimum and average market share of the listed browsers?

goal_question: List the main industry with highest total market value and its number of companies.
goal_sql: SELECT main_industry ,  count(*) FROM company GROUP BY main_industry ORDER BY sum(market_value) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find out 5 customers who most recently purchased something. List customers' first and last name.

goal_question: Give me a list of descriptions of the problems that are reported by the staff whose first name is Christop.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.problem_description FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.reported_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Christop"

goal_question: Find the name of department has the highest amount of students?
goal_sql: SELECT dept_name FROM student GROUP BY dept_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: List title of albums have the number of tracks greater than 10.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.title FROM albums AS T1 JOIN tracks AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.album_id GROUP BY T1.id HAVING count(T1.id)  >  10;

goal_question: Find the names of the chip models that are not used by any phone with full accreditation type.
goal_sql: SELECT model_name FROM chip_model EXCEPT SELECT chip_model FROM phone WHERE Accreditation_type  =  'Full'

goal_question: Find the name of the most expensive hardware product.
goal_sql: SELECT product_name FROM products WHERE product_type_code  =  'Hardware' ORDER BY product_price DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show member names without any registered branch.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM member WHERE member_id NOT IN (SELECT member_id FROM membership_register_branch)

goal_question: Show the names of players and names of their coaches.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.Player_name ,  T2.coach_name FROM player_coach AS T1 JOIN coach AS T2 ON T1.Coach_ID  =  T2.Coach_ID JOIN player AS T3 ON T1.Player_ID  =  T3.Player_ID

goal_question: What is the average age of the dogs who have gone through any treatments?
goal_sql: SELECT avg(age) FROM Dogs WHERE dog_id IN ( SELECT dog_id FROM Treatments )

goal_question: Which allergy has most number of students affected?
goal_sql: SELECT Allergy FROM Has_allergy GROUP BY Allergy ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show the maximum and minimum share count of different transaction types.
goal_sql: SELECT transaction_type_code ,  max(share_count) ,  min(share_count) FROM TRANSACTIONS GROUP BY transaction_type_code

goal_question: What is the total revenue of all companies whose main office is at Tokyo or Taiwan?
goal_sql: SELECT sum(revenue) FROM manufacturers WHERE Headquarter  =  'Tokyo' OR Headquarter  =  'Taiwan'

goal_question: Which semesters do not have any student enrolled? List the semester name.
goal_sql: SELECT semester_name FROM Semesters WHERE semester_id NOT IN( SELECT semester_id FROM Student_Enrolment )

goal_question: What are the names of the employees who authorised the destruction and the employees who destroyed the corresponding documents?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.employee_name ,  T3.employee_name FROM Documents_to_be_destroyed AS T1 JOIN Employees AS T2 ON T1.Destruction_Authorised_by_Employee_ID = T2.employee_id JOIN Employees AS T3 ON T1.Destroyed_by_Employee_ID = T3.employee_id;

goal_question: Who is the person that has no friend?
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM person EXCEPT SELECT name FROM PersonFriend

goal_question: Find the location and all games score of the school that has Clemson as its team name.
goal_sql: SELECT t2.All_Games ,  t1.location FROM university AS t1 JOIN basketball_match AS t2 ON t1.school_id  =  t2.school_id WHERE team_name  =  'Clemson'

goal_question: Find the name of all the cities and states.
goal_sql: SELECT town_city FROM addresses UNION SELECT state_province_county FROM addresses

goal_question: Which committees have delegates from both democratic party and liberal party?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Committee FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T2.Party  =  "Democratic" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Committee FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T2.Party  =  "Liberal"

goal_question: Find the id of instructors who taught a class in Fall 2009 but not in Spring 2010.
goal_sql: SELECT id FROM teaches WHERE semester  =  'Fall' AND YEAR  =  2009 EXCEPT SELECT id FROM teaches WHERE semester  =  'Spring' AND YEAR  =  2010

goal_question: Find the the name of the customers who have a loan with amount more than 3000.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.cust_name FROM customer AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.cust_id  =  T2.cust_id WHERE amount  >  3000

goal_question: Show all locations with only 1 station.
goal_sql: SELECT LOCATION FROM station GROUP BY LOCATION HAVING count(*)  =  1

goal_question: Find the average age of students who do not have any pet.
goal_sql: SELECT avg(age) FROM student WHERE stuid NOT IN (SELECT T1.stuid FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid)

goal_question: Show the ids of the faculty who don't participate in any activity.
goal_sql: SELECT FacID FROM Faculty EXCEPT SELECT FacID FROM Faculty_participates_in

goal_question: Which building does the instructor who teaches the most number of courses live in?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Building FROM COURSE AS T1 JOIN FACULTY AS T2 ON T1.Instructor  =  T2.FacID GROUP BY T1.Instructor ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Which organisation hired the most number of research staff? List the organisation id, type and detail.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.organisation_id ,  T1.organisation_type ,  T1.organisation_details FROM Organisations AS T1 JOIN Research_Staff AS T2 ON T1.organisation_id  =  T2.employer_organisation_id GROUP BY T1.organisation_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show the positions of the players from the team with name "Ryley Goldner".
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Position FROM match_season AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.Team  =  T2.Team_id WHERE T2.Name  =  "Ryley Goldner"

goal_question: How many assets does each third party company supply? List the count and the company id.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.company_id FROM Third_Party_Companies AS T1 JOIN Assets AS T2 ON T1.company_id  =  T2.supplier_company_id GROUP BY T1.company_id

goal_question: Which kind of policy type was chosen by the most customers?
goal_sql: SELECT Policy_Type_Code FROM Customer_Policies GROUP BY Policy_Type_Code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Which major has the most students?
goal_sql: SELECT Major FROM STUDENT GROUP BY major ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many documents do not have any expense?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Documents WHERE document_id NOT IN ( SELECT document_id FROM Documents_with_expenses )

goal_question: Show the headquarters that have at least two companies.
goal_sql: SELECT Headquarters FROM company GROUP BY Headquarters HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

goal_question: Which projects have no outcome? List the project details.
goal_sql: SELECT project_details FROM Projects WHERE project_id NOT IN ( SELECT project_id FROM Project_outcomes )

goal_question: list the names of the companies with more than 200 sales in the descending order of sales and profits.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM company WHERE Sales_in_Billion  >  200 ORDER BY Sales_in_Billion ,  Profits_in_Billion DESC

goal_question: Find the number of different departments in each school whose number of different departments is less than 5.
goal_sql: SELECT count(DISTINCT dept_name) ,  school_code FROM department GROUP BY school_code HAVING count(DISTINCT dept_name)  <  5

goal_question: which countries' tv channels are playing some cartoon written by Todd Casey?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.country FROM TV_Channel AS T1 JOIN cartoon AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.Channel WHERE T2.written_by  =  'Todd Casey'

goal_question: What is ids of the songs whose resolution is higher than the resolution of any songs with rating lower than 8?
goal_sql: SELECT f_id FROM song WHERE resolution  >  (SELECT max(resolution) FROM song WHERE rating  <  8)

goal_question: Find the name and gender of the candidate who got the highest support rate.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.name ,  t1.sex FROM people AS t1 JOIN candidate AS t2 ON t1.people_id  =  t2.people_id ORDER BY t2.support_rate DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the account details with the largest value or with value having char '5' in it?
goal_sql: SELECT max(Account_details) FROM Accounts UNION SELECT Account_details FROM Accounts WHERE Account_details LIKE "%5%"

goal_question: Find the names of scientists who are not working on the project with the highest hours.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM scientists EXCEPT SELECT T3.name FROM assignedto AS T1 JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.project  =  T2.code JOIN scientists AS T3 ON T1.scientist  =  T3.SSN WHERE T2.hours  =  (SELECT max(hours) FROM projects)

goal_question: Show the official names of the cities that have hosted more than one competition.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Official_Name FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID  =  T2.Host_city_ID GROUP BY T2.Host_city_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

goal_question: Find the pixels of the screen modes that are used by both phones with full accreditation types and phones with Provisional accreditation types.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.pixels FROM screen_mode AS t1 JOIN phone AS t2 ON t1.Graphics_mode  =  t2.screen_mode WHERE t2.Accreditation_type  =  'Provisional' INTERSECT SELECT t1.pixels FROM screen_mode AS t1 JOIN phone AS t2 ON t1.Graphics_mode  =  t2.screen_mode WHERE t2.Accreditation_type  =  'Full'

goal_question: Find the number of routes that have destination John F Kennedy International Airport.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.dst_apid WHERE T1.name  =  'John F Kennedy International Airport'

goal_question: Show the prices of the products named "Dining" or "Trading Policy".
goal_sql: SELECT Product_Price FROM Products WHERE Product_Name  =  "Dining" OR Product_Name  =  "Trading Policy"

goal_question: Which part fault requires the most number of skills to fix? List part id and name.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.part_id ,  T1.part_name FROM Parts AS T1 JOIN Part_Faults AS T2 ON T1.part_id  =  T2.part_id JOIN Skills_Required_To_Fix AS T3 ON T2.part_fault_id  =  T3.part_fault_id GROUP BY T1.part_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show names and seatings, ordered by seating for all tracks opened after 2000.
goal_sql: SELECT name ,  seating FROM track WHERE year_opened  >  2000 ORDER BY seating

goal_question: Which film actor (actress) starred the most films? List his or her first name, last name and actor id.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.first_name ,  T2.last_name ,  T2.actor_id FROM film_actor AS T1 JOIN actor AS T2 ON T1.actor_id  =  T2.actor_id GROUP BY T2.actor_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show the names of members and the dates of performances they attended in descending order of attendance of the performances.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Name ,  T3.Date FROM member_attendance AS T1 JOIN member AS T2 ON T1.Member_ID  =  T2.Member_ID JOIN performance AS T3 ON T1.Performance_ID  =  T3.Performance_ID ORDER BY T3.Attendance DESC

goal_question: Find the distinct student first names of all students that have grade point at least 3.8 in one course.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T3.Fname FROM ENROLLED_IN AS T1 JOIN GRADECONVERSION AS T2 JOIN STUDENT AS T3 ON T1.Grade  =  T2.lettergrade AND T1.StuID  =  T3.StuID WHERE T2.gradepoint  >=  3.8

goal_question: How many games were played in park "Columbia Park" in 1907?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM home_game AS T1 JOIN park AS T2 ON T1.park_id  =  T2.park_id WHERE T1.year = 1907 AND T2.park_name = 'Columbia Park';

goal_question: Find the subject ID, name of subject and the corresponding number of courses for each subject, and sort by the course count in ascending order.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.subject_id ,  T2.subject_name ,  COUNT(*) FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Subjects AS T2 ON T1.subject_id  =  T2.subject_id GROUP BY T1.subject_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC

goal_question: Show the police force shared by counties with location on the east and west.
goal_sql: SELECT Police_force FROM county_public_safety WHERE LOCATION  =  "East" INTERSECT SELECT Police_force FROM county_public_safety WHERE LOCATION  =  "West"

goal_question: Which district has the largest population?
goal_sql: SELECT district_name FROM district ORDER BY city_population DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the shortest duration and lowest rating of songs grouped by genre and ordered by genre?

goal_question: What are the names of nations speak both English and French?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "French"

goal_question: Find the codes of countries that have more than 50 players.
goal_sql: SELECT country_code FROM players GROUP BY country_code HAVING count(*)  >  50

goal_question: Show names, results and bulgarian commanders of the battles with no ships lost in the 'English Channel'.

goal_question: What is the most common mill type, and how many are there?
goal_sql: SELECT TYPE ,  count(*) FROM mill GROUP BY TYPE ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the theme and artist name for the exhibition with a ticket price higher than the average?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.theme ,  T2.name FROM exhibition AS T1 JOIN artist AS T2 ON T1.artist_id  =  T2.artist_id WHERE T1.ticket_price  >  (SELECT avg(ticket_price) FROM exhibition)

goal_question: Show the names of players and names of their coaches in descending order of the votes of players.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.Player_name ,  T2.coach_name FROM player_coach AS T1 JOIN coach AS T2 ON T1.Coach_ID  =  T2.Coach_ID JOIN player AS T3 ON T1.Player_ID  =  T3.Player_ID ORDER BY T3.Votes DESC

goal_question: How many Professors are in building NEB?

goal_question: What are the name and id of the team offering the lowest average salary?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.team_id FROM team AS T1 JOIN salary AS T2 ON T1.team_id = T2.team_id GROUP BY T1.team_id ORDER BY avg(T2.salary) ASC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: Show all student IDs with more than total 10 hours per week on all sports played.

goal_question: Show different tourist attractions' names, ids, and the corresponding number of visits.

goal_question: find the minimum and maximum number of products of all stores.

goal_question: Show the names of buildings except for those having an institution founded in 2003.

goal_question: What is the name of the breed with the most dogs?

goal_question: Show writers who have published a book with price more than 4000000.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Writer FROM book AS T1 JOIN publication AS T2 ON T1.Book_ID  =  T2.Book_ID WHERE T2.Price  >  4000000

goal_question: What are the distinct positions of the players from a country whose capital is Dublin?

goal_question: Please list the years of film market estimations when the market is in country "Japan" in descending order.

goal_sql: SELECT T1.Fname FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'cat' INTERSECT SELECT T1.Fname FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'dog'

goal_question: Show the teams that have both wrestlers eliminated by "Orton" and wrestlers eliminated by "Benjamin".

goal_question: Which shipping agent shipped the most documents? List the shipping agent name and the number of documents.

goal_question: Show the transaction type code that occurs the most frequently.

goal_question: Find the name and account balance of the customers who have loans with a total amount of more than 5000.

goal_question: Which movies have 'Deleted Scenes' as a substring in the special feature?

goal_question: List the status shared by more than two roller coaster.

goal_question: Show the most common type code across products.

goal_question: What is the product ID of the most frequently ordered item on invoices?

goal_question: Which student's age is older than 18 and is majoring in 600? List each student's first and last name.
