goal_question: Find the number of professors in accounting department.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM professor AS T1 JOIN department AS T2 ON T1.dept_code  =  T2.dept_code WHERE DEPT_NAME  =  "Accounting"

goal_question: Find the title, credit, and department name of courses that have more than one prerequisites?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.title ,  T1.credits , T1.dept_name FROM course AS T1 JOIN prereq AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id GROUP BY T2.course_id HAVING count(*)  >  1

goal_question: Show the first names and last names of customers without any account.
goal_sql: SELECT customer_first_name ,  customer_last_name FROM Customers EXCEPT SELECT T1.customer_first_name ,  T1.customer_last_name FROM Customers AS T1 JOIN Accounts AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id

goal_question: How many 'United Airlines' flights go to Airport 'ASY'?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM AIRLINES AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T2.Airline  =  T1.uid WHERE T1.Airline  =  "United Airlines" AND T2.DestAirport  =  "ASY"

goal_question: For model volvo, how many cylinders does the car with the least accelerate have?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.cylinders FROM CARS_DATA AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.MakeId WHERE T2.Model  =  'volvo' ORDER BY T1.accelerate ASC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: Find the name and gender of the staff who has been assigned the job of Sales Person but never Clerical Staff.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T1.staff_gender FROM staff AS T1 JOIN Staff_Department_Assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.job_title_code  =  "Sales Person" EXCEPT SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T1.staff_gender FROM staff AS T1 JOIN Staff_Department_Assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.job_title_code  =  "Clerical Staff"

goal_question: Find all phones that have word 'Full' in their accreditation types. List the Hardware Model name and Company name.
goal_sql: SELECT Hardware_Model_name ,  Company_name FROM phone WHERE Accreditation_type LIKE 'Full';

goal_question: Show the names of high school students and their corresponding number of friends.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.name ,  count(*) FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id GROUP BY T1.student_id

goal_question: Which districts have at least two addresses?
goal_sql: SELECT district FROM address GROUP BY district HAVING count(*)  >=  2

goal_question: Show the name of track with most number of races.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.name FROM race AS T1 JOIN track AS T2 ON T1.track_id  =  T2.track_id GROUP BY T1.track_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the semester when both Master students and Bachelor students got enrolled in.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T2.semester_id FROM Degree_Programs AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.degree_program_id  =  T2.degree_program_id WHERE degree_summary_name  =  'Master' INTERSECT SELECT DISTINCT T2.semester_id FROM Degree_Programs AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.degree_program_id  =  T2.degree_program_id WHERE degree_summary_name  =  'Bachelor'

goal_question: Find the number of trains for each station, as well as the station network name and services.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) ,  t1.network_name ,  t1.services FROM station AS t1 JOIN route AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.station_id GROUP BY t2.station_id

goal_question: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.mpg DESC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: Find the id and name of the staff who has been assigned for the shortest period.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.staff_id ,  T1.staff_name FROM staff AS T1 JOIN Staff_Department_Assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id ORDER BY date_assigned_to - date_assigned_from LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the email of the student with first name "Emma" and last name "Rohan"?
goal_sql: SELECT email_address FROM Students WHERE first_name  =  "Emma" AND last_name  =  "Rohan"

goal_question: What are the forename and surname of the driver who has the smallest laptime?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.forename ,  T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN laptimes AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid ORDER BY T2.milliseconds LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is average age of male for different job title?
goal_sql: SELECT avg(age) ,  job FROM Person WHERE gender  =  'male' GROUP BY job

goal_question: List the top 5 genres by number of tracks. List genres name and total tracks.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name ,  COUNT(*) FROM genres AS T1 JOIN tracks AS T2 ON T2.genre_id  =  T1.id GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 5;

goal_question: display the first and last name, department, city, and state province for each employee.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T2.department_name ,  T3.city ,  T3.state_province FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id JOIN locations AS T3 ON T2.location_id  =  T3.location_id

goal_question: Find the busiest source airport that runs most number of routes in China.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.src_apid WHERE T1.country  =  'China' GROUP BY T1.name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the average and minimum age of captains in different class?
goal_sql: SELECT avg(age) ,  min(age) ,  CLASS FROM captain GROUP BY CLASS

goal_question: Find the average age of female (sex is F) students who have secretary votes in the spring election cycle.
goal_sql: SELECT avg(T1.Age) FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  SECRETARY_Vote WHERE T1.Sex  =  "F" AND T2.Election_Cycle  =  "Spring"

goal_question: What are the first names of customers who have not rented any films after '2005-08-23 02:06:01'?
goal_sql: SELECT first_name FROM customer WHERE customer_id NOT IN( SELECT customer_id FROM rental WHERE rental_date  >  '2005-08-23 02:06:01' )

goal_question: Find the name of the employee who got the highest one time bonus.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.name FROM employee AS t1 JOIN evaluation AS t2 ON t1.Employee_ID  =  t2.Employee_ID ORDER BY t2.bonus DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the title of the course that is offered by more than one department.
goal_sql: SELECT title FROM course GROUP BY title HAVING count(*)  >  1

goal_question: Which store owns most items?
goal_sql: SELECT store_id FROM inventory GROUP BY store_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the birth places that are shared by at least two people?
goal_sql: SELECT Birth_Place FROM people GROUP BY Birth_Place HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

goal_question: Find the appelations that produce wines after the year of 2008 but not in Central Coast area.
goal_sql: SELECT Appelation FROM WINE WHERE YEAR  >  2008 EXCEPT SELECT Appelation FROM APPELLATIONS WHERE Area  =  "Central Coast"

goal_question: Show the names and main services for train stations that have the top three total number of passengers.
goal_sql: SELECT name ,  main_services FROM station ORDER BY total_passengers DESC LIMIT 3

goal_question: Find the id and local authority of the station with has the highest average high temperature.
goal_sql: SELECT t2.id ,  t2.local_authority FROM weekly_weather AS t1 JOIN station AS t2 ON t1.station_id  =  t2.id GROUP BY t1.station_id ORDER BY avg(high_temperature) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the first names and last names of male (sex is M) faculties who live in building NEB.
goal_sql: SELECT Fname ,  Lname FROM FACULTY WHERE sex  =  "M" AND Building  =  "NEB"

goal_question: List the name of the colleges whose enrollment is greater 18000 sorted by the college's name.
goal_sql: SELECT cName FROM College WHERE enr  >  18000 ORDER BY cName

goal_question: Which department has more than 1 head at a time? List the id, name and the number of heads.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.department_id ,  T1.name ,  count(*) FROM management AS T2 JOIN department AS T1 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id GROUP BY T1.department_id HAVING count(*)  >  1

goal_question: Find the student ID and middle name for all the students with at most two enrollments.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.student_id ,  T2.middle_name FROM Student_Course_Enrolment AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING COUNT(*)  <=  2

goal_question: Give me the product type, name and price for all the products supplied by supplier id 3.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.product_type_code ,  T2.product_name ,  T2.product_price FROM product_suppliers AS T1 JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.product_id  =  T2.product_id WHERE T1.supplier_id  =  3

goal_question: List the names of people that are not poker players.
goal_sql: SELECT Name FROM people WHERE People_ID NOT IN (SELECT People_ID FROM poker_player)

goal_question: Show the name for regions not affected.
goal_sql: SELECT region_name FROM region WHERE region_id NOT IN (SELECT region_id FROM affected_region)

goal_question: find the code of the country where has the greatest number of players.
goal_sql: SELECT country_code FROM players GROUP BY country_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show the addresses of the buildings that have apartments with more than 2 bathrooms.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.building_address FROM Apartment_Buildings AS T1 JOIN Apartments AS T2 ON T1.building_id  =  T2.building_id WHERE T2.bathroom_count  >  2

goal_question: Find the emails of customers who has filed a complaints of the product with the most complaints.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.email_address FROM customers AS t1 JOIN complaints AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id GROUP BY t1.customer_id ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the first and last names of all the female (sex is F) students who have president votes.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Fname ,  T1.LName FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.President_VOTE WHERE T1.sex  =  "F"

goal_question: In which year were most departments established?
goal_sql: SELECT creation FROM department GROUP BY creation ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Which distinctive models are produced by maker with the full name General Motors or weighing more than 3500?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Model  =  T2.Model JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T3 ON T2.Maker  =  T3.Id JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T1.MakeId  =  T4.Id WHERE T3.FullName  =  'General Motors' OR T4.weight  >  3500;

goal_question: What are the nationalities that are shared by at least two people?
goal_sql: SELECT Nationality FROM people GROUP BY Nationality HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

goal_question: How many official languages does Afghanistan have?
goal_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.Name  =  "Afghanistan" AND IsOfficial  =  "T"

goal_question: What is the project id and detail for the project with at least two documents?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.project_id ,  T1.project_details FROM Projects AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.project_id  =  T2.project_id GROUP BY T1.project_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

goal_question: Which dogs have not cost their owner more than 1000 for treatment? List the dog names.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM Dogs WHERE dog_id NOT IN( SELECT dog_id FROM Treatments GROUP BY dog_id HAVING sum(cost_of_treatment)  >  1000 )

goal_question: List the types of competition that have at most five competitions of that type.
goal_sql: SELECT Competition_type FROM competition GROUP BY Competition_type HAVING COUNT(*)  <=  5

goal_question: What is the total number of products that are in orders with status "Cancelled"?
goal_sql: SELECT sum(t2.order_quantity) FROM customer_orders AS t1 JOIN order_items AS t2 ON t1.order_id  =  t2.order_id WHERE t1.order_status  =  "Cancelled"

goal_question: Find the name and age of the visitor who bought the most tickets at once.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.name ,  t1.age FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id ORDER BY t2.num_of_ticket DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the visit date and details of the visitor whose detail is 'Vincent'?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Visit_Date ,  T2.Visit_Details FROM VISITORS AS T1 JOIN VISITS AS T2 ON T1.Tourist_ID  =  T2.Tourist_ID WHERE T1.Tourist_Details  =  "Vincent"

goal_question: What is the id of the product that was ordered the most often?
goal_sql: SELECT product_id FROM order_items GROUP BY product_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the name of customers who are living in Colorado?
goal_sql: SELECT t1.customer_name FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_addresses AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN addresses AS t3 ON t2.address_id  =  t3.address_id WHERE t3.state_province_county  =  "Colorado"

goal_question: Show the names of pilots and fleet series of the aircrafts they have flied with in ascending order of the rank of the pilot.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.Pilot_name ,  T2.Fleet_Series FROM pilot_record AS T1 JOIN aircraft AS T2 ON T1.Aircraft_ID  =  T2.Aircraft_ID JOIN pilot AS T3 ON T1.Pilot_ID  =  T3.Pilot_ID ORDER BY T3.Rank

goal_question: What are the regions that use English or Dutch?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Region FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" OR T2.Language  =  "Dutch"

goal_question: What are the total number of Domestic Passengers of airports that contain the word "London".
goal_sql: SELECT sum(Domestic_Passengers) FROM airport WHERE Airport_Name LIKE "%London%"

goal_question: Show the names of journalists and the number of events they reported.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM news_report AS T1 JOIN event AS T2 ON T1.Event_ID  =  T2.Event_ID JOIN journalist AS T3 ON T1.journalist_ID  =  T3.journalist_ID GROUP BY T3.Name

goal_question: Find the name and rank of the 3 youngest winners across all matches.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT winner_name ,  winner_rank FROM matches ORDER BY winner_age LIMIT 3

goal_question: Which professionals live in a city containing the substring 'West'? List his or her role, street, city and state.

goal_question: Find the name of the person who has friends with age above 40 but not under age 30?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend IN (SELECT name FROM Person WHERE age  >  40) EXCEPT SELECT T1.name FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend IN (SELECT name FROM Person WHERE age  <  30)

goal_question: What are the notes of the death events which has substring 'East'?
goal_sql: SELECT note FROM death WHERE note LIKE '%East%'

goal_question: What are the death and injury situations caused by the ship with tonnage 't'?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.killed ,  T1.injured FROM death AS T1 JOIN ship AS t2 ON T1.caused_by_ship_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.tonnage  =  't'

goal_question: Find the names and number of works of all artists who have at least one English songs.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.artist_name ,  count(*) FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name WHERE T2.languages  =  "english" GROUP BY T2.artist_name HAVING count(*)  >=  1

goal_question: How many car makers are there in each continents? List the continent name and the count.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Continent ,  count(*) FROM CONTINENTS AS T1 JOIN COUNTRIES AS T2 ON T1.ContId  =  T2.continent JOIN car_makers AS T3 ON T2.CountryId  =  T3.Country GROUP BY T1.Continent;

goal_question: Which classroom has the most students?
goal_sql: SELECT classroom FROM list GROUP BY classroom ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the ids of all distinct customers who made order after some orders that were Cancelled.

goal_question: Show all the faculty ranks and the number of students advised by each rank.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.rank ,  count(*) FROM Faculty AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.FacID  =  T2.advisor GROUP BY T1.rank

goal_question: Find the physician who was trained in the most expensive procedure?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN trained_in AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.physician JOIN procedures AS T3 ON T3.code  =  T2.treatment ORDER BY T3.cost DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What states have at least two representatives?
goal_sql: SELECT State FROM representative GROUP BY State HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

goal_question: Retrieve the title of the paper that has the largest number of authors.
goal_sql: SELECT t2.title FROM authorship AS t1 JOIN papers AS t2 ON t1.paperid  =  t2.paperid WHERE t1.authorder  =  (SELECT max(authorder) FROM authorship)

goal_question: What are the product id and product type of the cheapest product?

goal_question: Find the name of dorms that do not have any amenity

goal_question: Which region is the city Kabul located in?

goal_question: What is the name of the course that has the most student enrollment?

goal_question: Find the name and email of the user followed by the least number of people.

goal_question: List all of the ids for left-footed players with a height between 180cm and 190cm.

goal_question: Show names of musicals and the number of actors who have appeared in the musicals.

goal_question: Show the name of cities in the county that has the largest number of police officers.

goal_question: Find the number of routes for each source airport and the airport name.

goal_sql: SELECT T2.document_name FROM Templates AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.template_id  =  T2.template_id WHERE T1.template_type_code  =  "BK"

goal_question: Show the names of journalists and the names of the events they reported in ascending order
goal_sql: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Name FROM news_report AS T1 JOIN event AS T2 ON T1.Event_ID  =  T2.Event_ID JOIN journalist AS T3 ON T1.journalist_ID  =  T3.journalist_ID ORDER BY T2.Event_Attendance ASC

goal_question: What are the names of customers using the most popular payment method?

goal_question: Which stadium name contains the substring "Bank"?

goal_question: What are the codes of the countries that do not speak English and whose government forms are not Republic?

goal_question: What are the names of body builders whose total score is higher than 300?

goal_question: What is the name and country of origin of the artist who released a song that has "love" in its title?

goal_question: Select the name and price of all products with a price larger than or equal to $180, and sort first by price (in descending order), and then by name  (in ascending order).
goal_sql: SELECT name ,  price FROM products WHERE price  >=  180 ORDER BY price DESC ,  name ASC

goal_question: Show the most common builder of railways.
goal_sql: SELECT Builder FROM railway GROUP BY Builder ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the total revenue of companies whose revenue is larger than the revenue of some companies based in Austin.

goal_question: Which template type code has most number of templates?

goal_question: How many assets can each parts be used in? List the part name and the number.

goal_question: Find the number of different airports which are the destinations of the American Airlines.
goal_sql: SELECT count(DISTINCT dst_apid) FROM airlines AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.alid  =  T2.alid WHERE T1.name  =  'American Airlines'

goal_question: List the object number of railways that do not have any trains.
goal_sql: SELECT ObjectNumber FROM railway WHERE Railway_ID NOT IN (SELECT Railway_ID FROM train)

goal_question: What are the names of the songs whose rating is below the rating of all songs in English?

goal_question: display job title and average salary of employees.

goal_question: List the organisation id with the maximum outcome count, and the count.

goal_question: Show the pilot positions that have both pilots joining after year 2005 and pilots joining before 2000.
goal_sql: SELECT POSITION FROM pilot WHERE Join_Year	 <  2000 INTERSECT SELECT POSITION FROM pilot WHERE Join_Year	 >  2005

goal_question: Find all first-grade students who are NOT taught by OTHA MOYER. Report their first and last names.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.firstname ,  T1.lastname FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom WHERE T1.grade  =  1 EXCEPT SELECT T1.firstname ,  T1.lastname FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom WHERE T2.firstname  =  "OTHA" AND T2.lastname  =  "MOYER"

goal_question: How many distinct kinds of camera lenses are used to take photos of mountains in the country 'Ethiopia'?

goal_question: Show the headquarters that have both companies in banking industry and companies in oil and gas industry.

goal_question: Find the first names and offices of all instructors who have taught some course and also find the course description.

goal_question: Find the names of all instructors in Comp. Sci. department with salary > 80000.

goal_question: What is the document type code with most number of documents?

goal_question: What are the distinct name of the mills built by the architects who have also built a bridge longer than 80 meters?

goal_question: What is the payment method code used by the most orders?

goal_question: What are the names of wines that are more expensive then all wines made in the year 2006?

goal_question: Show the fleet series of the aircrafts flied by pilots younger than 34

goal_question: Show the minimum, average, maximum order quantity of all invoices.

goal_question: How many patients do each physician take care of? List their names and number of patients they take care of.

goal_question: Which enzyme names have the substring "ALA"?

goal_question: Return all the committees that have delegates from Democratic party.

goal_question: Find all the films longer than 100 minutes, or rated PG, except those who cost more than 200 for replacement. List the titles.
goal_sql: SELECT title FROM film WHERE LENGTH  >  100 OR rating  =  'PG' EXCEPT SELECT title FROM film WHERE replacement_cost  >  200

goal_question: Find the number of amenities for each of the dorms that can accommodate more than 100 students.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.dormid FROM dorm AS T1 JOIN has_amenity AS T2 ON T1.dormid  =  T2.dormid WHERE T1.student_capacity  >  100 GROUP BY T1.dormid

goal_question: Show the date of the tallest perpetrator.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Date FROM people AS T1 JOIN perpetrator AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T1.Height DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show all cities without a branch having more than 100 memberships.
goal_sql: SELECT city FROM branch EXCEPT SELECT city FROM branch WHERE membership_amount  >  100

goal_question: Find the email and phone number of the customers who have never filed a complaint before.
goal_sql: SELECT email_address ,  phone_number FROM customers WHERE customer_id NOT IN (SELECT customer_id FROM complaints)

goal_question: What are the name and id of the team with the most victories in 2008 postseason?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.name ,  T1.team_id_winner FROM postseason AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.team_id_winner  =  T2.team_id_br WHERE T1.year  =  2008 GROUP BY T1.team_id_winner ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: Find the name and id of the item with the highest average rating.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.title ,  T1.i_id FROM item AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.i_id GROUP BY T2.i_id ORDER BY avg(T2.rating) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many dogs have not gone through any treatment?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Dogs WHERE dog_id NOT IN ( SELECT dog_id FROM Treatments )

goal_question: Find the names of employees who never won any award in the evaluation.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM employee WHERE Employee_ID NOT IN (SELECT Employee_ID FROM evaluation)

goal_question: Find the last names of the members of the club "Bootup Baltimore".
goal_sql: SELECT t3.lname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Bootup Baltimore"

goal_question: What is the date of enrollment of the course named "Spanish"?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.date_of_enrolment FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Student_Course_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id WHERE T1.course_name  =  "Spanish"

goal_question: Find the program which most number of students are enrolled in. List both the id and the summary.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.degree_program_id ,  T1.degree_summary_name FROM Degree_Programs AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.degree_program_id  =  T2.degree_program_id GROUP BY T1.degree_program_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find names of colleges with enrollment greater than that of some (at least one) college in the FL state.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT cName FROM college WHERE enr  >  (SELECT min(enr) FROM college WHERE state  =  'FL')

goal_question: what are name and phone number of patients who had more than one appointment?
goal_sql: SELECT name ,  phone FROM appointment AS T1 JOIN patient AS T2 ON T1.patient  =  T2.ssn GROUP BY T1.patient HAVING count(*)  >  1

goal_question: Find the total and average amount of settlements.
goal_sql: SELECT sum(settlement_amount) ,  avg(settlement_amount) FROM settlements

goal_question: Show names and phones of customers who do not have address information.
goal_sql: SELECT customer_name ,  customer_phone FROM customers WHERE customer_id NOT IN (SELECT customer_id FROM customer_address_history)

goal_question: How many professionals did not operate any treatment on dogs?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Professionals WHERE professional_id NOT IN ( SELECT professional_id FROM Treatments )

goal_question: Which policy type has the most records in the database?
goal_sql: SELECT policy_type_code FROM available_policies GROUP BY policy_type_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are names of stations that have average bike availability above 10 and are not located in San Jose city?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM station AS T1 JOIN status AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.station_id GROUP BY T2.station_id HAVING avg(bikes_available)  >  10 EXCEPT SELECT name FROM station WHERE city  =  "San Jose"

goal_question: How many countries does each continent have? List the continent id, continent name and the number of countries.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.ContId ,  T1.Continent ,  count(*) FROM CONTINENTS AS T1 JOIN COUNTRIES AS T2 ON T1.ContId  =  T2.Continent GROUP BY T1.ContId;

goal_question: Show the name of the shop that have the largest quantity of devices in stock.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Shop_Name FROM stock AS T1 JOIN shop AS T2 ON T1.Shop_ID  =  T2.Shop_ID GROUP BY T1.Shop_ID ORDER BY SUM(T1.quantity) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show all document ids, names and the number of paragraphs in each document.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.document_id ,  T2.document_name ,  count(*) FROM Paragraphs AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id GROUP BY T1.document_id

goal_question: For all the faults of different parts, what are all the decriptions of the skills required to fix them? List the name of the faults and the skill description.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.fault_short_name ,  T3.skill_description FROM Part_Faults AS T1 JOIN Skills_Required_To_Fix AS T2 ON T1.part_fault_id  =  T2.part_fault_id JOIN Skills AS T3 ON T2.skill_id  =  T3.skill_id

goal_question: Find the first names of all professors in the Accounting department who is teaching some course and the class room.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.emp_fname ,  T1.class_room FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.prof_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN professor AS T3 ON T2.emp_num  =  T3.emp_num JOIN department AS T4 ON T4.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code WHERE T4.dept_name  =  'Accounting'

goal_question: What is the country of origin of the artist who is female and produced a song in Bangla?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.country FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name WHERE T1.gender  =  "Female" AND T2.languages  =  "bangla"

goal_question: which countries' tv channels are playing some cartoon written by Todd Casey?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.country FROM TV_Channel AS T1 JOIN cartoon AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.Channel WHERE T2.written_by  =  'Todd Casey'

goal_question: What are all info of students who registered courses but not attended courses?
goal_sql: SELECT * FROM student_course_registrations WHERE student_id NOT IN (SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance)

goal_question: Show all information on the airport that has the largest number of international passengers.
goal_sql: SELECT * FROM airport ORDER BY International_Passengers DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show names of musicals which have at least three actors.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Name FROM actor AS T1 JOIN musical AS T2 ON T1.Musical_ID  =  T2.Musical_ID GROUP BY T1.Musical_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  3

goal_question: What is the total ticket expense of the visitors whose membership level is 1?
goal_sql: SELECT sum(t2.Total_spent) FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id WHERE t1.Level_of_membership  =  1

goal_question: Show the first and last name of all the faculty members who participated in some activity, together with the number of activities they participated in.
goal_sql: SELECT  T1.fname ,  T1.lname ,  count(*) ,  T1.FacID FROM Faculty AS T1 JOIN Faculty_participates_in AS T2 ON T1.facID  =  T2.facID GROUP BY T1.FacID

goal_question: Find the last name and hire date of the professor who is in office DRE 102.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.emp_lname ,  T1.emp_hiredate FROM employee AS T1 JOIN professor AS T2 ON T1.emp_num  =  T2.emp_num WHERE T2.prof_office  =  'DRE 102'

goal_question: Find the names of all instructors whose name includes the substring “dar”.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM instructor WHERE name LIKE '%dar%'

goal_question: What is the name of the student who has the highest total credits in the History department.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM student WHERE dept_name  =  'History' ORDER BY tot_cred DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the minimum and maximum number of bathrooms of all the apartments?
goal_sql: SELECT min(bathroom_count) ,  max(bathroom_count) FROM Apartments

goal_question: List the weight of the body builders who have snatch score higher than 140 or have the height greater than 200.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.weight FROM body_builder AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.people_id  =  T2.people_id WHERE T1.snatch  >  140 OR T2.height  >  200;

goal_question: Find the name of the department which has the highest average salary of professors.
goal_sql: SELECT dept_name FROM instructor GROUP BY dept_name ORDER BY avg(salary) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Retrieve the country that has published the most papers.
goal_sql: SELECT t1.country FROM inst AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.instid  =  t2.instid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid GROUP BY t1.country ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: List the first and last name of all players who are left / L hand in the order of birth date.
goal_sql: SELECT first_name ,  last_name FROM players WHERE hand  =  'L' ORDER BY birth_date

goal_question: What is the id and name of the enzyme with most number of medicines that can interact as 'activator'?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.name FROM enzyme AS T1 JOIN medicine_enzyme_interaction AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.enzyme_id WHERE T2.interaction_type  =  'activitor' GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show all member names who are not in charge of any event.
goal_sql: SELECT member_name FROM member EXCEPT SELECT T1.member_name FROM member AS T1 JOIN party_events AS T2 ON T1.member_id  =  T2.member_in_charge_id

goal_question: For each customer who has at least two orders, find the customer name and number of orders made.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.customer_name ,  count(*) FROM orders AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id GROUP BY T2.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

goal_question: Find the number of professors with a Ph.D. degree in each department.
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) ,  dept_code FROM professor WHERE prof_high_degree  =  'Ph.D.' GROUP BY dept_code

goal_question: What are the details of the lots which are not used in any transactions?
goal_sql: SELECT lot_details FROM Lots EXCEPT SELECT T1.lot_details FROM Lots AS T1 JOIN transactions_lots AS T2 ON T1.lot_id  =  T2.lot_id

goal_question: list the card number of all members whose hometown address includes word "Kentucky".
goal_sql: SELECT card_number FROM member WHERE Hometown LIKE "%Kentucky%"

goal_question: What are the product ids for the problems reported by Christop Berge with closure authorised by Ashley Medhurst?
goal_sql: SELECT product_id FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.reported_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Christop" AND T2.staff_last_name = "Berge" INTERSECT SELECT product_id FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.closure_authorised_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Ashley" AND T2.staff_last_name = "Medhurst"

goal_question: What are the response received dates for the documents described as 'Regular' or granted with more than 100?

goal_question: Find the name of students who didn't take any course from Biology department.

goal_question: Show party names and the number of events for each party.

goal_question: Show the transaction type code that occurs the fewest times.
goal_sql: SELECT transaction_type_code FROM TRANSACTIONS GROUP BY transaction_type_code ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the name of bank branch that provided the greatest total amount of loans to customers with credit score is less than 100.

goal_question: List the id of students who attended  statistics courses in the order of attendance date.

goal_question: Which staff have contacted which engineers? List the staff name and the engineer first name and last name.

goal_question: Show all paragraph ids and texts for the document with name 'Welcome to NY'.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.paragraph_id ,   T1.paragraph_text FROM Paragraphs AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id WHERE T2.Document_Name  =  'Welcome to NY'

goal_question: Show card type codes with at least 5 cards.

goal_question: What are the dates of transactions with at least 100 share count or amount bigger than 100?
goal_sql: SELECT date_of_transaction FROM TRANSACTIONS WHERE share_count  >=  100 OR amount_of_transaction  >=  100

goal_question: How many tracks are in the AAC audio file media type?

goal_question: What are the names of the directors who made exactly one movie?
goal_sql: SELECT director FROM Movie GROUP BY director HAVING count(*)  =  1

goal_question: Find the name and email of the user whose name contains the word ‘Swift’.
goal_sql: SELECT name ,  email FROM user_profiles WHERE name LIKE '%Swift%'

goal_question: List the name and count of each product in all orders.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.product_name ,  count(*) FROM orders AS T1 JOIN order_items AS T2 JOIN products AS T3 ON T1.order_id = T2.order_id AND T2.product_id = T3.product_id GROUP BY T3.product_id

goal_question: Whic`h unique cities are in  Asian countries where Chinese is the official language?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T3.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode JOIN city AS T3 ON T1.Code  =  T3.CountryCode WHERE T2.IsOfficial  =  'T' AND T2.Language  =  'Chinese' AND T1.Continent  =  "Asia"

goal_question: What are the order dates of orders with price higher than 1000?

goal_question: What are the distinct positions of the players from a country whose capital is Dublin?
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Position FROM country AS T1 JOIN match_season AS T2 ON T1.Country_id  =  T2.Country WHERE T1.Capital  =  "Dublin"

goal_question: Which contact channel has been used by the customer with name "Tillman Ernser"?

goal_question: How many enzymes do not have any interactions?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM enzyme WHERE id NOT IN ( SELECT enzyme_id FROM medicine_enzyme_interaction );

goal_question: Find the names of the visitors whose membership level is higher than 4, and order the results by the level from high to low.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM visitor WHERE Level_of_membership  >  4 ORDER BY Level_of_membership DESC

goal_question: Show the name of the party that has the most delegates.

goal_sql: SELECT yearid FROM hall_of_fame GROUP BY yearid ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: Find the name of the teacher who teaches the largest number of students.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.firstname ,  T2.lastname FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom GROUP BY T2.firstname ,  T2.lastname ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What is the name of the patient who made the most recent appointment?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM patient AS T1 JOIN appointment AS T2 ON T1.ssn = T2.patient ORDER BY T2.start DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the name of the user who gives the most reviews.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM useracct AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.u_id  =  T2.u_id GROUP BY T2.u_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the title of course that is provided by Statistics but not Psychology departments.

goal_question: Find the average ranking for each player and their first name.

goal_question: What is the title of the course that was offered at building Chandler during the fall semester in the year of 2010?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.title FROM course AS T1 JOIN SECTION AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id WHERE building  =  'Chandler' AND semester  =  'Fall' AND YEAR  =  2010

goal_sql: SELECT T1.campus FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN faculty AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.campus WHERE T2.year  =  2003 ORDER BY T2.faculty DESC LIMIT 1

goal_sql: SELECT T1.product_id FROM product_suppliers AS T1 JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.product_id  =  T2.product_id WHERE T1.supplier_id  =  2 AND T2.product_price  >  (SELECT avg(product_price) FROM products)

goal_question: Find the name of the first 5 customers.
goal_sql: SELECT customer_name FROM Customers ORDER BY date_became_customer LIMIT 5

goal_question: Which bike traveled the most often in zip code 94002?

goal_question: What are the issue dates of volumes associated with the artist aged 23 or younger?

goal_question: Find the names of users who have more than one tweet.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN tweets AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.uid GROUP BY T2.uid HAVING count(*)  >  1

goal_question: What is the name of tracks whose genre is Rock?

goal_question: Find the name of captains whose rank are either Midshipman or Lieutenant.

goal_question: Show the publishers that have publications with price higher than 10000000 and publications with price lower than 5000000.

goal_question: List all the document names which contains "CV".

goal_question: Show the stadium names without any concert.

goal_question: What is the age of student Linda Smith?

goal_question: What is the name of the patient who made the most recent appointment?

goal_question: Find all the policy types that are used by more than 2 customers.
goal_sql: SELECT policy_type_code FROM policies GROUP BY policy_type_code HAVING count(*)  >  2

goal_question: What are the ids of stations that are located in San Francisco and have average bike availability above 10.
goal_sql: SELECT id FROM station WHERE city  =  "San Francisco" INTERSECT SELECT station_id FROM status GROUP BY station_id HAVING avg(bikes_available)  >  10

goal_question: What is the location shared by most counties?
goal_sql: SELECT LOCATION FROM county_public_safety GROUP BY LOCATION ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Which project made the most number of outcomes? List the project details and the project id.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.project_details ,  T1.project_id FROM Projects AS T1 JOIN Project_outcomes AS T2 ON T1.project_id  =  T2.project_id GROUP BY T1.project_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the login name of the course author that teaches the course with name "advanced database".
goal_sql: SELECT T1.login_name FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors AS T1 JOIN Courses AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id WHERE T2.course_name  =  "advanced database"

goal_question: What is the name of the product with the color description 'yellow'?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.product_name FROM products AS T1 JOIN ref_colors AS T2 ON T1.color_code  =  T2.color_code WHERE T2.color_description  =  'yellow'

goal_question: What is the least common media type in all tracks?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Name FROM MEDIATYPE AS T1 JOIN TRACK AS T2 ON T1.MediaTypeId  =  T2.MediaTypeId GROUP BY T2.MediaTypeId ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many car makers are there in each continents? List the continent name and the count.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Continent ,  count(*) FROM CONTINENTS AS T1 JOIN COUNTRIES AS T2 ON T1.ContId  =  T2.continent JOIN car_makers AS T3 ON T2.CountryId  =  T3.Country GROUP BY T1.Continent;

goal_question: How many cards does customer Art Turcotte have?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Customers_cards AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.customer_first_name  =  "Art" AND T2.customer_last_name  =  "Turcotte"

goal_question: What is the id, forname and surname of the driver who had the first position in terms of laptime at least twice?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.driverid ,  T1.forename ,  T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN laptimes AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid WHERE POSITION  =  '1' GROUP BY T1.driverid HAVING count(*)  >=  2

goal_question: For each injury accident, find the date of the game and the name of the injured player in the game, and sort the results in descending order of game season.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.date ,  T2.player FROM game AS T1 JOIN injury_accident AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.game_id ORDER BY T1.season DESC

goal_question: What are the names and years of the movies that has the top 3 highest rating star?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.title ,  T2.year FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID ORDER BY T1.stars DESC LIMIT 3

goal_question: Find the name of rooms whose price is higher than the average price.
goal_sql: SELECT roomName FROM Rooms WHERE basePrice  >  ( SELECT avg(basePrice) FROM Rooms );

goal_question: Show the residences that have both a player of gender "M" and a player of gender "F".
goal_sql: SELECT Residence FROM player WHERE gender  =  "M" INTERSECT SELECT Residence FROM player WHERE gender  =  "F"

goal_question: What are the first names and last names of students with address in Wisconsin state?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.first_name ,  T2.last_name FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.address_id  =  T2.address_id WHERE T1.state_province_county  =  "Wisconsin"

goal_question: Which countries do not have a stadium that was opened after 2006?
goal_sql: SELECT country FROM stadium EXCEPT SELECT country FROM stadium WHERE opening_year  >  2006

goal_question: Find the titles of items whose rating is higher than the average review rating of all items.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.title FROM item AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.i_id WHERE T2.rating  >  (SELECT avg(rating) FROM review)

goal_question: Which film is rented at a fee of 0.99 and has less than 3 in the inventory? List the film title and id.
goal_sql: SELECT title ,  film_id FROM film WHERE rental_rate  =  0.99 INTERSECT SELECT T1.title ,  T1.film_id FROM film AS T1 JOIN inventory AS T2 ON T1.film_id  =  T2.film_id GROUP BY T1.film_id HAVING count(*)  <  3

goal_question: Show names of ships involved in a mission launched after 1928.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Name FROM mission AS T1 JOIN ship AS T2 ON T1.Ship_ID  =  T2.Ship_ID WHERE T1.Launched_Year  >  1928

goal_question: What is the song in the volume with the maximum weeks on top?
goal_sql: SELECT Song FROM volume ORDER BY Weeks_on_Top DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Find the name and age of the person who is a friend of both Dan and Alice.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.age FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend  =  'Dan' INTERSECT SELECT T1.name ,   T1.age FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend  =  'Alice'

goal_question: Find the names of the products with length smaller than 3 or height greater than 5.
goal_sql: SELECT catalog_entry_name FROM catalog_contents WHERE LENGTH  <  3 OR width  >  5

goal_question: What are the durations of the longest and the shortest tracks in milliseconds?
goal_sql: SELECT max(Milliseconds) ,  min(Milliseconds) FROM TRACK

goal_question: What are the actual delivery dates of orders with quantity 1?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Actual_Delivery_Date FROM Customer_Orders AS T1 JOIN ORDER_ITEMS AS T2 ON T1.Order_ID  =  T2.Order_ID WHERE T2.Order_Quantity  =  1

goal_question: List the first name of all the professionals along with the description of the treatment they have done.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.first_name ,  T3.treatment_type_description FROM professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id JOIN Treatment_types AS T3 ON T2.treatment_type_code  =  T3.treatment_type_code

goal_question: What are the sale details and dates of transactions with amount smaller than 3000?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.sales_details ,  T2.date_of_transaction FROM SALES AS T1 JOIN TRANSACTIONS AS T2 ON T1.sales_transaction_id  =  T2.transaction_id WHERE T2.amount_of_transaction  <  3000

goal_question: List the hardware model name for the phons that were produced by "Nokia Corporation" but whose screen mode type is not Text.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Hardware_Model_name FROM screen_mode AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Graphics_mode = T2.screen_mode WHERE t2.Company_name  =  "Nokia Corporation" AND T1.Type != "Text";

goal_question: What are the maximum and minimum age of students with major 600?
goal_sql: SELECT max(Age) ,  min(Age) FROM STUDENT WHERE Major  =  600

goal_question: How long does student Linda Smith spend on the restaurant in total?
goal_sql: SELECT sum(Spent) FROM Student JOIN Visits_Restaurant ON Student.StuID = Visits_Restaurant.StuID WHERE Student.Fname = "Linda" AND Student.Lname = "Smith";

goal_question: Show the locations of parties and the names of the party hosts in ascending order of the age of the host.
goal_sql: SELECT T3.Location ,  T2.Name FROM party_host AS T1 JOIN HOST AS T2 ON T1.Host_ID  =  T2.Host_ID JOIN party AS T3 ON T1.Party_ID  =  T3.Party_ID ORDER BY T2.Age

goal_question: What are names for top three branches with most number of membership?
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM branch ORDER BY membership_amount DESC LIMIT 3

goal_question: Find the different first names and cities of the students who have allergy to milk or cat.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.fname ,  T1.city_code FROM Student AS T1 JOIN Has_Allergy AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid WHERE T2.Allergy  =  "Milk" OR T2.Allergy  =  "Cat"

goal_question: Find the number of different products that are produced by companies at different headquarter cities.
goal_sql: SELECT count(DISTINCT T1.name) ,  T2.Headquarter FROM products AS T1 JOIN manufacturers AS T2 ON T1.Manufacturer  =  T2.code GROUP BY T2.Headquarter

goal_question: Find the names of customers who either have an deputy policy or uniformed policy.
goal_sql: SELECT DISTINCT t2.customer_details FROM policies AS t1 JOIN customers AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id WHERE t1.policy_type_code  =  "Deputy" OR t1.policy_type_code  =  "Uniform"

goal_question: For each Orange county campus, report the number of degrees granted after 2000.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.campus ,  sum(T2.degrees) FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN degrees AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.campus WHERE T1.county  =  "Orange" AND T2.year  >=  2000 GROUP BY T1.campus

goal_question: Show names, results and bulgarian commanders of the battles with no ships lost in the 'English Channel'.
goal_sql: SELECT name ,  RESULT ,  bulgarian_commander FROM battle EXCEPT SELECT T1.name ,  T1.result ,  T1.bulgarian_commander FROM battle AS T1 JOIN ship AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.lost_in_battle WHERE T2.location  =  'English Channel'

goal_question: How many lessons taken by customer with first name as Rylan and last name as Goodwin were completed?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Lessons AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.first_name = "Rylan" AND T2.last_name = "Goodwin" AND T1.lesson_status_code = "Completed";

goal_question: What is the season of the game which causes the player 'Walter Samuel' to get injured?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.season FROM game AS T1 JOIN injury_accident AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.game_id WHERE T2.player  =  'Walter Samuel'

goal_question: What is the city_code of the city that the most students live in?
goal_sql: SELECT city_code FROM STUDENT GROUP BY city_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the names of tourist attractions that can be reached by walk or is at address 660 Shea Crescent?
goal_sql: SELECT T2.Name FROM Locations AS T1 JOIN Tourist_Attractions AS T2 ON T1.Location_ID  =  T2.Location_ID WHERE T1.Address  =  "660 Shea Crescent" OR T2.How_to_Get_There  =  "walk"

goal_question: What is the average height of the players from the college named 'Yale University'?
goal_sql: SELECT avg(T1.height) FROM player AS T1 JOIN player_college AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id JOIN college AS T3 ON T3.college_id  =  T2.college_id WHERE T3.name_full  =  'Yale University';

goal_question: Show the ids of high schoolers who have friends and are also liked by someone else.
goal_sql: SELECT student_id FROM Friend INTERSECT SELECT liked_id FROM Likes

goal_question: Which customer, who has made at least one payment, has spent the least money? List his or her first name, last name, and the id.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T1.customer_id FROM customer AS T1 JOIN payment AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id ORDER BY sum(amount) ASC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Select the project names which are not assigned yet.
goal_sql: SELECT Name FROM Projects WHERE Code NOT IN (SELECT Project FROM AssignedTo)

goal_question: What is the name and job title of the staff who was assigned the latest?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T2.job_title_code FROM staff AS T1 JOIN staff_department_assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id ORDER BY T2.date_assigned_to DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: How many documents are using the template with type code 'PPT'?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM Documents AS T1 JOIN Templates AS T2 ON T1.Template_ID  =  T2.Template_ID WHERE T2.Template_Type_Code  =  'PPT'

goal_question: Find the name of project that continues for the longest time.
goal_sql: SELECT name FROM projects ORDER BY hours DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: For the cars with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest horsepower?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Cylinders  =  4 ORDER BY T2.horsepower DESC LIMIT 1;

goal_question: Show institution names along with the number of proteins for each institution.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.institution ,  count(*) FROM institution AS T1 JOIN protein AS T2 ON T1.institution_id  =  T2.institution_id GROUP BY T1.institution_id

goal_question: What is the last name and office of the professor from the history department?
goal_sql: SELECT T1.emp_lname ,  T2.prof_office FROM employee AS T1 JOIN professor AS T2 ON T1.emp_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN department AS T3 ON T2.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code WHERE T3.dept_name  =  'History'

goal_question: Find the name of the department that has the fewest members.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.DName FROM DEPARTMENT AS T1 JOIN MEMBER_OF AS T2 ON T1.DNO  =  T2.DNO GROUP BY T2.DNO ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

goal_question: Show director with the largest number of show times in total.
goal_sql: SELECT T2.directed_by FROM schedule AS T1 JOIN film AS T2 ON T1.film_id  =  T2.film_id GROUP BY T2.directed_by ORDER BY sum(T1.show_times_per_day) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: List all tracks bought by customer Daan Peeters.
goal_sql: SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN invoice_lines AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.track_id JOIN invoices AS T3 ON T3.id = T2.invoice_id JOIN customers AS T4 ON T4.id = T3.customer_id WHERE T4.first_name = "Daan" AND T4.last_name = "Peeters";

goal_question: Find the total account balance of each customer from Utah or Texas.
goal_sql: SELECT sum(acc_bal) FROM customer WHERE state  =  'Utah' OR state  =  'Texas'

goal_question: Which origin has most number of flights?
goal_sql: SELECT origin FROM Flight GROUP BY origin ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

goal_question: What are the mascots for schools with enrollments above the average?
goal_sql: SELECT mascot FROM school WHERE enrollment  >  (SELECT avg(enrollment) FROM school)

goal_question: Find number of tracks in each genre?
goal_sql: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.name FROM genres AS T1 JOIN tracks AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.genre_id GROUP BY T1.name;

goal_question: What is the total number of unique official languages spoken in the countries that are founded before 1930?
goal_sql: SELECT count(DISTINCT T2.Language) FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE  IndepYear  <  1930 AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"
